# Canonical identity for this repository's owner.
#
# History before 2026-07 was authored under two earlier addresses. The commits
# themselves were rewritten to the canonical identity, but this file is kept as
# a backstop so that any clone still carrying pre-rewrite objects — and any
# future commit that slips through with an old address — still resolves to one
# person in `git log`, `git shortlog`, `git blame` and GitHub's UI.
#
# Matching is by email alone, so both "Wei Zhou" and "wei zhou" spellings map.
wei <zhouwei008@gmail.com> <boyi.liang@gmail.com>
wei <zhouwei008@gmail.com> <98p@sina.com>

# Normalise the name on the canonical address too. GitHub stamps squash-merge
# commits with the *account profile* display name ("wei zhou"), not the local
# git config name, so this recurs on every squash merge regardless of history
# rewrites. Fixing it at the source means changing the GitHub profile name.
wei <zhouwei008@gmail.com> <zhouwei008@gmail.com>
